NoLimit

webmachine/bitcask proof of concept for a disk backed, fast k/v cache

TODO: 

* merging?

DISCLAIMER:

i am not an erlang programmer, critique is welcome and encouraged


INSTALL:

0) brew install erlang
1) git clone git://github.com:capotej/nolimit.git
2) cd nolimit
3) make
4) ./start.sh


USAGE: 

SET
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/ -d "foo=bar"

GET
curl http://localhost:8000/?key=foo


TESTING/BENCHMARKING: (requires only ruby + curl command)
0) ./start.sh
1) ruby misc/readwrite.rb
 - or - 
2) ruby misc/write.rb
